race.description: Elders Real Estate Batemans Bay Super Maiden Plate
race.comment: BLUE MONDAY (12) eye-catching debut when closed off strongly for an unlucky second over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Finds a much easier contest and should prove too smart for these from the inside gate. BRUTAL ADVANCE (1) deep into his preparation and assess on his fast finishing second at Hawkesbury three starts back. Blinkers come off from the low draw and looks the main danger. COLD MIST (2) from the in-form Paul Murray stable and strips fitter after closing late for a respectable fourth over 1200m at Queanbeyan. Has the speed to get across from the gate and not to be overlooked. ZEEMA (11) knocked up late at her first run back when fourth over 1400m at Kembla Grange. Placed second-up in the past and stays in the contest. I DOUBT IT (7) back without a trial when an even fifth first-up. Looks the best of the rest.
